            . I am an <rs id="t18170702-13-viclabel72" type="occupation">accountant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-13-victim151 t18170702-13-viclabel72"></join>. On the 12th of June, between four and five o'clock in the afternoon. I was walking along the <placeName id="t18170702-13-crimeloc73">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-13-crimeloc73" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-13-crimeloc73" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-13-off70 t18170702-13-crimeloc73"></join>, a person tapped me on the shoulder at the <placeName id="t18170702-13-crimeloc74">corner of Beaufort-buildings</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-13-crimeloc74" type="placeName" value="corner of Beaufort-buildings"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-13-crimeloc74" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-13-off70 t18170702-13-crimeloc74"></join>, I turned round and a young man told me my pocket was picked-The prisoner was running. I immediately pursued, and saw my handkerchief on the pavement, some person picked it up and gave it to me. I continued running, and at the corner of Exeter-change the prisoner was stopped and given into my charge. I believe him to be the man I was pursuing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170702-13-person153">
                  ELISHA 
                  TURNER
               <interp inst="t18170702-13-person153" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
